        <br id="view_the_waitlist">
        <hr>
        <h3>View the Waitlist</h3>
        <br>
        <div style="text-align:left;">
        <ol>
            <li>Click 'Active'/'Waiting'/'Notified'/'Confirmed' on the navigation bar to view Wait Lists.</li>
            <ul>
                <li>'Active' contains 'Waiting' and 'Notified' Guests.</li>
                <li>'Waiting' contains Guests you haven't notified to come in yet.</li>
                <li>'Notified' contains Guests you <em>have</em> notified to come in.</li>
                <li>'Confirmed' contains Guests you <em>have</em> notified AND who have confirmed that they are coming in.</li>
                <li>'Archived' contains Guests who have been:</li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Notified to come in More Than 1 Hour ago.</li>
                    <li>Waiting for More Than 2 Hours.</li>
                </ul>
                <li>Click any Guest Name in 'Active'/'Waiting'/'Notified'/'Confirmed'/'Archived' to view the Guest's Wait Session Details.</li>
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Please note the 'Number Of People' and 'Seating Preference' for each Wait Session <em>before</em> you notify a Guest to come in.</b></li>
                </ul>
            </ul>
        </ol>
        </div>
        <br id="notify_guests">
        <hr>
        <h3>Notify Guests</h3>
        <br>
        <div style="text-align:left;">
        <ul>
            <li><b>To notify a Guest to come in, you can either send them an SMS OR Phone them:</b></li>
            <ul>
                <li>Click on a Guest Name in 'Waiting'.</li>
                <li>Click <b>'Notify By SMS'</b></li>
                <ul>
                    <li>The Guest will receive an SMS on their cell phone asking them to come in.</li>
                    <li>The Guest will be transferred from 'Waiting' to 'Notified'.</li>
                    <li><b style="color:red;">Please notify a Guest to come in by SMS only <em>ONCE</em> by clicking the 'Notify By SMS' button. (This is because each SMS costs about 1 cent.)</b></li>
                </ul>
                <li><b>Alternatively, you can also phone the Guest to ask them to come in. If you <em>have</em> phoned them, please click 'Already Phoned Guest' to transfer them from 'Waiting' to 'Notified'.</b></li>
                <li><b style="color:#003BEF;">Consider bookmarking the app's 'Waiting' page on your cell phone (app URL: <a href='http://bit.ly/sugarwaitstaff' target='_blank' style="color:#0094FF;">bit.ly/sugarwaitstaff</a>) and (double-clicking/copying and pasting) the Guest's phone number to call them.</b></li>
                <li>The time of 'First Notification' (by SMS or phone) will be recorded in the Guest's Wait Session Details.</li>
            </ul>
        </ul>
        <ul>
            <li><b>Please <em>phone</em> when you can and use SMS for busier times since SMS costs money. Thanks!</b></li>
        </ul>
        </div>
        <br id="clean_up">
        <hr>
        <h3>Clean up (Archive) old Wait Sessions</h3>
        <br>
        <div style="text-align:left;">
        <ul>
            <li>Click 'Waiting'/'Notified'/'Confirmed' and then 'Archive Old Sessions' to remove old Wait Sessions from the 'Waiting'/'Notified'/'Confirmed' lists.</li>
            <ul>
                <li>This removes Guests from the lists who have been (1) waiting for more than 2 hours <em>or</em> (2) notified more than 1 hour ago.</li>
                <li>Guests will be transferred from 'Waiting'/'Notified'/'Confirmed' to 'Archived'.</li>
                <li><b>'Archived' only shows Guests who started their wait after 00:00AM (Midnight) today AND were archived</b></li>
                <li>You can still view a Guest's Wait Session Details after they've been archived by clicking the Guest Name.</li>
                <li><b>You cannot 'un-archive' a guest to transfer them back to 'Waiting'/'Notified'/'Confirmed' lists.</b></li>
            </ul>
        </ul>
        </div>
        <br id="create_wait">
        <hr>
        <h3>Create a Wait Session</h3>
        <br>
        <div style="text-align:left;">
        <ol>
            <li>Click 'Create New' to create a new Wait Session for a Guest.</li>
            <li>Fill out the form.</li>
            <li>The Guest will be added to the 'Waiting' and 'Active' lists.</li>
        </ol>
        <ul>
            <li><b>If the Guest is <em>not</em> carrying a Smart Phone:</b></li>
            <ul>
                <li><b>The 'Create New' form has a checkbox for 'Is the Guest carrying a smart phone?'</b></li>
                <li><b>Use 7806556817 or your own phone number (you won't receive spam).</b></li>
                <li><b>When a table is ready, click 'Already Phoned Guest' to transfer the Guest from 'Waiting' to 'Notified'.</b></li>
                <li><b>Please personally fetch the Guest from outside.</b></li>
            </ul>
        </ul>
        </div>
        <br id="update_wait">
        <hr>
        <h3>Update Wait Session Details</h3>
        <br>
        <div style="text-align:left;">
        <p><b>You will only need to update a Wait Session if a Guest asks you to update their details.</b></p>
        <ul>
            <li>Click the Guest's name under 'Waiting'. Click 'Update Session', fill out and submit the form.</li>
            <ul>
                <li>Your updates will be apparent in the Guest's Wait Session Details.</li>
                <li><b>Note: The app also allows the Guest to update their details, so a Guest's Wait Session Details may change even though <em>you</em> haven't made changes.</b></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <br id="delete_wait">
        <hr>
        <h3>Delete a Wait Session</h3>
        <br>
        <div style="text-align:left;">
        <ul>
            <li><b>Since you can 'archive' Wait Sessions, you will not need to delete a Guest's Wait Session. This functionality is included for 'just-in-case' scenarios</b>, for example, if a guest asks you to delete their information.</li>
            <li><b>In general, please 'archive' Wait Sessions instead of deleting since I will be collecting data to include 'Estimated Wait Time' to improve the app.</b></li>
            <li>Click the Guest's name under 'Waitlist'/'Notified'/'Confirmed'/'Archived'. Click 'Delete Session'. <b>The Wait Session will be deleted forever.</b></li>
        </ul>
        </div>
        <br id="guest_experience">
